notesStmt.note: Several leaves are more or less damaged.

User's notes: folio 3r (upper left-hand margin): Shemu᾿el Leṿi ben Avraham ha-Leṿi: inscribed, dated (5)452 ( 1692); folio 359v: Avraham ben Shemu᾿el ha-Leṿi; Yitsḥaḳ ha-Leṿi, and another one partially illegible.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A volume belonging to a series of Karaite service-books, which have been originally deposited in the Karaite Synagogue in Jerusalem.

msItem.title: A series of services for fast days and Purim
An office used at marriages (a fragment)

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; Section titles written in larger square characters. Catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental square and semi-cursive script of the 16th to 17th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Karaite Prayer Book. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2530.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882; inscribed, folio [ 360v].
